Thank you.

16:08.696 --> 16:10.669
Excuse me again.
Excuse me.

16:11.610 --> 16:13.617
Sorry.
Thank. Thank you all.

16:23.542 --> 16:26.147
I'm sorry. I'm.
Okay, merry.

16:28.523 --> 16:29.699
You're a monster!

16:29.892 --> 16:31.841
You're ruining christmas for everybody!

16:32.230 --> 16:34.217
He was. He was like that, I swear.

16:36.996 --> 16:38.578
Mr. Monk, we gotta keep moving.

16:39.144 --> 16:41.404
They think I'm a monster.
Did you see their faces?

16:41.470 --> 16:43.877
- They hate me.
- No, Mr. Monk, they don't hate you.

16:43.892 --> 16:44.929
Not really.

16:46.036 --> 16:47.329
That's definitely the guy.

16:47.624 --> 16:48.646
I now it!

16:48.988 --> 16:51.784
Let's keep walking.
I think one of 'em had a rope.

16:51.799 --> 16:53.041
I can't live like this.

16:53.219 --> 16:54.793
The trial could be a year away.

16:54.808 --> 16:56.838
I have to tell them my side
of the story.

16:56.853 --> 16:58.821
No, Mr. Monk.
I've heard your side of the story

16:58.836 --> 17:01.012
and I love you,
and I don't think it's a good idea.

17:01.027 --> 17:02.897
This is just a P.R.
Problem.

17:03.112 --> 17:06.455
When your dad sold that tainted
toothpaste from China, what did he do?

17:07.579 --> 17:11.157
He went on the news and he told his side
of the story. He took the offensive.

17:11.670 --> 17:13.367
I can be as offensive as your father.

17:13.450 --> 17:14.660
I'm sure you can.

17:14.963 --> 17:16.623
You know, that woman Brandy Barber,

17:17.063 --> 17:18.511
she's, she's Been calling me.

17:18.762 --> 17:20.896
She wants me to do her show.
I think I'm gonna do it.

17:20.911 --> 17:22.733
No no, Mr. Monk.
I've seen her show.

17:22.790 --> 17:25.832
She's not a real journalist.
She'll rip you apart!

17:26.737 --> 17:27.737
Natalie.

17:29.199 --> 17:30.766
You're forgetting one thing.

17:30.979 --> 17:31.979
The truth.

17:32.230 --> 17:34.236
See, I have the truth on my side.

17:36.419 --> 17:37.432
My god.

17:39.870 --> 17:40.893
Merry christmas.

17:49.749 --> 17:51.177
You gotta unbutton the shirt.

17:51.215 --> 17:52.771
No, I'm good.

17:52.786 --> 17:54.112
I'll just hold it.

17:54.594 --> 17:55.597
Like Sinatra.

17:55.914 --> 17:57.322
You gotta unbutton the shirt.

17:58.108 --> 17:59.111
No, really.

17:59.241 --> 18:01.226
I'm, I'm really not
comfortable unbuttoning.

18:01.241 --> 18:02.259
Brandy!

18:03.591 --> 18:05.192
Okay, all right, all right.

18:05.355 --> 18:06.995
Look, it's unbuttoned, all right?

18:07.268 --> 18:08.599
Hi, excuse me, sorry.

18:08.675 --> 18:10.607
I've known Mr. Monk for a long time,

18:10.622 --> 18:12.410
and he really loves christmas.

18:12.425 --> 18:13.855
It's his favorite holiday.

18:14.579 --> 18:16.765
You know, he comes to our school
christmas pageant

18:17.054 --> 18:18.148
every single year

18:18.517 --> 18:21.681
- and he decorates our tree.
- He does. And here's the thing.

18:21.696 --> 18:23.386
He's just a little bit particular,

18:23.401 --> 18:25.319
just about certain things, so...

18:25.391 --> 18:26.701
Yeah, he's,

18:27.028 --> 18:28.360
- special.
- In a good way.

18:28.379 --> 18:29.566
- Yeah.
- Good special.

18:29.581 --> 18:31.646
So if you would mind just being like
a little bit.

18:31.685 --> 18:33.393
Little bit sensitive
that would be great.

18:33.408 --> 18:36.082
Don't worry Ms. Teeger. Know all about
attention deficit disorder.

18:36.097 --> 18:38.222
I did a primetime special on it.
Won a local emmy.

18:38.237 --> 18:40.293
- It's not a.d.
- It's not attention deficit.

18:40.308 --> 18:42.426
- No, he just has compulsions.
- Yeah.

18:42.441 --> 18:44.433
- You know, rituals.
- He's a big boy.

18:44.489 --> 18:46.013
Jerry, let's do this.

18:46.422 --> 18:47.760
<i>Everybody salon.</i>

18:47.856 --> 18:49.888
We're rolling in five,

18:49.934 --> 18:51.496
four, three...

18:54.078 --> 18:55.332
Adrian Monk, hello.

18:55.376 --> 18:57.325
Hello and merry christmas.

18:57.372 --> 18:59.516
Thank you for inviting us into
your beautiful home.

18:59.531 --> 19:00.548
You're welcome.

19:00.800 --> 19:01.803
Merry christmas.

19:01.833 --> 19:03.107
You've already said that.

19:03.942 --> 19:05.679
Well, you.
You can't say it enough.

19:06.290 --> 19:07.641
This is my favorite holiday.

19:11.682 --> 19:13.185
The tree.
Yeah, this is my tree.

19:16.353 --> 19:17.761
It's quite festive

19:18.530 --> 19:19.842
because that's how I feel.

19:21.675 --> 19:22.774
<i>Presents.</i>

19:23.255 --> 19:24.760
About christmas.

19:25.512 --> 19:27.267
<i>No, the presents.</i>

19:28.320 --> 19:29.478
Some gifts...

19:29.947 --> 19:31.472
For christmas.
Christmas gifts.

19:31.502 --> 19:33.169
Yes, we were looking at those earlier.

19:33.355 --> 19:35.979
They're all from your assistant,
Natalie Teeger.

19:36.315 --> 19:38.630
Well, no, not.
Not this one.

19:39.774 --> 19:41.088
This is from my wife.

19:41.337 --> 19:42.573
That would be Trudy.

19:42.588 --> 19:44.621
She died ten years ago, didn't she?

19:44.810 --> 19:46.281
And you still haven't opened it.

19:46.648 --> 19:49.396
That's
very unusual behavior, wouldn't you say?

19:50.567 --> 19:52.573
Would you like some cookies?

19:52.996 --> 19:54.599
- Yeah, so...
- Would you like some?

19:54.661 --> 19:56.494
We made some cookies this morning.

19:56.933 --> 19:59.109
- Festive christmas cookies.
- No, thank you.

19:59.233 --> 20:02.538
You received a psychological discharge
from the police department, didn't you?

20:04.006 --> 20:05.067
Yes. Yes.

20:05.202 --> 20:06.346
Mr. Monk,

20:06.623 --> 20:07.754
how does it feel

20:07.769 --> 20:10.108
to be the most reviled man
in California?

20:11.508 --> 20:12.510
Bad.

20:13.923 --> 20:14.926
Have you seen

20:15.296 --> 20:16.300
these?

20:18.530 --> 20:19.543
I.

20:19.708 --> 20:22.196
- I don't think "santacide" is a word.
- <i>It's not.</i>

20:22.485 --> 20:23.932
It is now, thanks to you.

20:24.669 --> 20:27.157
We've all heard Mr. Kenworthy's
side of the story.

20:27.427 --> 20:28.787
He rented a Santa costume

20:28.802 --> 20:30.794
and was on that roof trying
to give toys away

20:30.809 --> 20:32.938
in the true spirit of christmas.

20:33.786 --> 20:34.804
Merry christmas.

20:34.819 --> 20:36.217
You can stop saying that now.

20:36.410 --> 20:38.075
Mr. Kenworthy said you went

20:38.090 --> 20:40.296
up to that roof
and just started shooting.

20:40.599 --> 20:42.027
That's not what happened.

20:42.316 --> 20:44.197
Why don't you tell us your side
of the story?

20:44.289 --> 20:45.298
Thank you.

20:46.006 --> 20:47.482
Well, first off,

20:48.027 --> 20:50.150
I want to say
<i>to any children watching</i>

20:51.065 --> 20:52.261
I did not shoot

20:52.384 --> 20:53.985
Santa Claus.
That man,

20:54.472 --> 20:55.979
was not Santa Claus.

20:57.208 --> 20:58.944
There's no such thing as Santa Claus.

21:05.207 --> 21:07.021
No, that can't be good.

21:11.964 --> 21:13.237
You knew that, right?

21:17.152 --> 21:18.329
Here's the thing.

21:19.293 --> 21:20.613
That was not my gun.

21:20.677 --> 21:21.736
That was his gun.

21:22.042 --> 21:23.042
He dropped it.

21:23.057 --> 21:24.351
Then he attacked me.

21:24.366 --> 21:26.403
Is this the gun you're referring to?

21:26.576 --> 21:28.158
Where did.
Where did you get that?

21:28.323 --> 21:30.621
I'm a reporter, Mr. Monk.
I have my sources.

21:30.872 --> 21:33.264
It's a rather distinctive
weapon, isn't it?

21:33.522 --> 21:36.633
A snub-nose.38
with an antique ivory handle.

21:36.667 --> 21:39.059
As you can see,
part of the handle is missing.

21:39.098 --> 21:42.302
- Yes, it's broken.
- Which brings me to my final question.

21:42.688 --> 21:45.317
We received an anonymous phone call
from one of your neighbors.

21:46.058 --> 21:47.062
Which one?

21:47.840 --> 21:48.843
He didn't say.

21:48.901 --> 21:50.039
It was anonymous.

21:50.673 --> 21:51.785
He did say

21:51.849 --> 21:55.180
he saw you burying something
behind your building last night.

21:56.089 --> 21:57.227
Burying something?

21:57.418 --> 22:00.168
My producer and I came by
and dug it up.

22:00.593 --> 22:02.799
I have it right here.
We wanted to show it to you

22:02.814 --> 22:05.025
before we turn it over
to the authorities.

22:06.845 --> 22:07.848
Do you

22:08.061 --> 22:09.064
recognize it?

22:13.876 --> 22:15.053
It's a perfect fit.

22:16.615 --> 22:18.429
Do you still say it wasn't your gun?

22:35.379 --> 22:36.420
Mr. Kenworthy.

22:37.427 --> 22:38.643
It's Leland Stottlemeyer.

22:39.241 --> 22:40.245
Randy Disher.

22:40.480 --> 22:42.918
- We spoke at the hospital.
- Yes, of course.

22:43.005 --> 22:45.551
- Come in. Thank you.
- We thought you might want these back.

22:47.587 --> 22:49.149
So this is the north pole?

22:49.592 --> 22:51.334
It's not exactly like I pictured it.

22:51.467 --> 22:53.802
It's not the taj mahal,
but it's all I need.

22:55.328 --> 22:56.544
Everything's there.

22:56.679 --> 22:58.357
Except for one rubber snake.

22:58.464 --> 23:00.393
It's for my nephew.
I didn't think you'd mind.

23:00.831 --> 23:02.142
He doesn't have a nephew.

23:02.777 --> 23:04.583
- I have nephew.
- He doesn't have a nephew.

23:04.598 --> 23:06.597
Benjamin.
His name's Benjamin.

23:06.654 --> 23:07.756
He's nine years old.

23:08.278 --> 23:09.281
See.

23:10.953 --> 23:11.956
How's the wing?

23:12.787 --> 23:14.845
I'll live. Guess it could've been worse?

23:15.484 --> 23:16.487
Yep.

23:16.502 --> 23:19.134
I see you're still in touch
with some of your old parolees.

23:19.710 --> 23:20.790
Thought you retired.

23:21.085 --> 23:22.517
Well, I call 'em when I can.

23:22.637 --> 23:25.318
- They're good guys.
- Yeah, I know some of these good guys.

23:25.588 --> 23:27.788
Burglary, <i>Grand Theft Auto...</i>

23:27.846 --> 23:28.848
Attempted murder.

23:29.877 --> 23:31.642
I help 'em out when I can.
What can I say?

23:32.233 --> 23:34.298
Everybody deserves a second chance,
right?

23:37.795 --> 23:38.798
What?

23:39.564 --> 23:41.069
What were you doing up there

23:41.374 --> 23:42.821
Michael, on that roof?

23:44.305 --> 23:45.540
Givin' away some toys.

23:45.692 --> 23:47.271
What can I say?
I love christmas!

23:47.322 --> 23:48.339
Come on, Buddy.

23:48.907 --> 23:50.721
There's nobody here.
It's just you and me.

23:51.425 --> 23:52.717
- And me.
- And him.

23:54.274 --> 23:55.470
Is that why you're here?

23:56.170 --> 23:57.424
To accuse me of something?

23:59.476 --> 24:00.826
Why don't you take a hike?

24:01.159 --> 24:02.163
Both of you!

24:02.579 --> 24:04.913
That gun was found in your friend's
back yard, not mine.

24:07.500 --> 24:08.696
Yeah, that may be true.

24:09.316 --> 24:11.149
But here's the problem, Kris Kringle.

24:12.599 --> 24:13.899
Either you're lying

24:14.626 --> 24:15.957
or Adrian Monk is lying.

24:18.313 --> 24:19.392
Merry christmas.

24:38.865 --> 24:40.022
Merry christmas.

24:40.273 --> 24:41.508
Merry christmas.

24:59.198 --> 25:01.590
Thank god! That man has a knife!

25:01.628 --> 25:03.326
Yeah, I know.

25:18.340 --> 25:21.716
Well, apparently she did not go gentle
into that good night.

25:22.605 --> 25:25.067
We found this can of pepper spray
under her body.

25:25.134 --> 25:26.134
Witnesses?

25:26.168 --> 25:28.456
Couple of neighbors said
they heard some screaming.

25:28.471 --> 25:30.470
One said she heard a clanging sound.

25:30.753 --> 25:33.836
- Clanging?
- That's the guy! That's Adrian Monk!

25:35.731 --> 25:37.325
Crawl back under your rock!

25:37.340 --> 25:40.140
It's all right. Just ignore them.
Just pretend like they're not there.

25:40.187 --> 25:41.761
Why did you shoot Santa Claus?

25:41.776 --> 25:43.933
Hey, Monk,
how many reindeer you kill today?

25:47.558 --> 25:50.047
Okay, her name is Alice Dubois.

25:50.106 --> 25:52.340
She's 64, retired teacher,

25:52.461 --> 25:55.279
she lived here in apartment b17

25:55.294 --> 25:57.667
with a beagle and some house plants.

25:57.682 --> 26:01.099
She worked
part time in the macmillan Museum

26:01.283 --> 26:03.826
in the gift shop.
Hey! Hey, gimme a break!

26:03.841 --> 26:06.371
- I didn't shoot anyone!
- Randy. Randy, what are you doing?

26:06.391 --> 26:07.883
They're lumping us all together.

26:08.841 --> 26:11.407
So what do you think?
Wrong place, wrong time?

26:11.625 --> 26:12.705
I don't think so.

26:13.299 --> 26:14.619
No, he was waiting.

26:15.076 --> 26:16.116
Waiting for her.

26:16.488 --> 26:17.775
These cigarette butts...

26:18.453 --> 26:21.527
He was camped out here for
probably 48 minutes.

26:22.379 --> 26:24.154
- 48 minutes?
- Yeah, look.

26:26.098 --> 26:27.864
The ends are all smooshed in.

26:27.909 --> 26:29.291
I only see one match.

26:29.779 --> 26:31.103
He was chain-smoking.

26:32.161 --> 26:33.502
Eight cigarettes.

26:33.948 --> 26:35.935
Figure six minutes per cigarette.

26:35.957 --> 26:37.465
- 48 minutes.
- Yeah.

26:37.480 --> 26:40.730
How do you live with yourself, monster!

26:42.508 --> 26:43.392
Hey.

26:43.715 --> 26:44.993
Hey, who threw that?

26:45.905 --> 26:48.268
- Who threw that egg?
- Oh, my god!

26:48.409 --> 26:49.952
It's okay. I'm all right.

26:49.994 --> 26:51.936
I got it right here on my sleeve.

26:52.053 --> 26:53.905
- Who threw the egg? And right here.
- Yeah.

26:54.134 --> 26:56.350
And here.
And then I got some here.

26:56.792 --> 26:59.047
Is that gonna come out?
Is that gonna come out!

26:59.510 --> 27:00.679
Is that gonna come out.

27:00.694 --> 27:02.964
Who would bring an egg to a crime scene?

27:03.388 --> 27:05.009
You two wait across the street.

27:06.127 --> 27:07.361
Wait across the street.

27:09.396 --> 27:10.592
Cover them, protect 'em.

27:24.077 --> 27:25.080
God.

27:28.809 --> 27:30.488
Hey, those are my wipes.

27:31.078 --> 27:33.293
You can use them if you want to.

27:44.366 --> 27:45.369
What?

27:45.799 --> 27:47.131
- Brian.
- Mr. M?

27:47.169 --> 27:48.548
Do you have a cause of death?

27:48.563 --> 27:50.625
It's unofficial.
It looks like blunt trauma.

27:50.678 --> 27:51.881
Eight, maybe nine hits.

27:52.311 --> 27:53.814
- From what?
- You tell me.

27:55.773 --> 27:57.200
Something sharp and heavy.

27:57.971 --> 27:59.920
- Curved edge.
- Weird, huh?

28:00.436 --> 28:02.932
- Maybe a frying pan?
- Or a bell. A bell?

28:07.756 --> 28:10.346
- What is it?
- She was hit on the right side.

28:10.911 --> 28:13.471
So that means the attacker
was left-handed, right?

28:13.486 --> 28:15.044
Or his right arm was in a sling.

28:15.063 --> 28:16.066
A sling.

28:16.731 --> 28:19.799
Look, there's Candy Canes on the ground.
There's three impressions

28:19.814 --> 28:23.189
like from a tripod.
One of those charity collection pots.

28:23.350 --> 28:25.981
- Mr. Monk, what are you saying?
- I think I know who did this.

28:25.996 --> 28:26.801
Who?

28:30.562 --> 28:31.662
Santa Claus.

28:32.807 --> 28:33.986
- Who?
- Santa Claus!

28:34.001 --> 28:35.131
No, not again!

28:35.146 --> 28:38.016
No! No! No! No!

28:38.073 --> 28:40.234
No, Mr. Monk, please no.

28:41.305 --> 28:44.108
All right, ladies. Let's do it again.
From the top.

28:45.598 --> 28:46.614
How's the arm?

28:46.629 --> 28:48.466
We'll find a doctor
when we get to ecuador.

28:48.481 --> 28:50.480
Were supposed to be in ecuador
four days ago,

28:50.495 --> 28:51.963
sippin margaritas on the beach.

28:51.978 --> 28:54.228
We caught a bad break, a minor setback.

28:54.243 --> 28:56.268
I thought that was your job,
Mr. Mastermind.

28:56.283 --> 28:57.613
To anticipate minor setbacks.

28:57.628 --> 29:00.648
Well how was he supposed to know that
cop Adrian Monk was gonna be there?

29:00.663 --> 29:02.676
Would you forget about Monk?
It was a fluke.

29:03.185 --> 29:04.477
But the plan is solid.

29:05.170 --> 29:06.791
Thorn and me took care of the old lady.

29:07.363 --> 29:09.160
Yeah, she won't be coming
to work tomorrow.

29:09.212 --> 29:10.581
She had a death in the family.

29:12.106 --> 29:14.080
Carl,
did you call your boss at the museum?

29:14.138 --> 29:16.682
No problem. I'll be working
the gift shop 2:00 to 6:00.

29:16.697 --> 29:18.292
That's it then, we go tomorrow.

29:18.393 --> 29:19.898
Closing time, 6:00.

29:20.822 --> 29:21.633
Okay,

29:22.146 --> 29:23.157
I made a list.

29:23.404 --> 29:24.600
Did you check it twice?

29:33.198 --> 29:35.474
Adrian, you've got to stop
blaming yourself.

29:36.926 --> 29:39.080
What happened on that roof
is not your fault.

29:39.095 --> 29:41.665
If the man attacked you,
then it's self defense.

29:41.680 --> 29:43.055
Nobody believes me.

29:44.388 --> 29:46.433
My word against Santa Claus.

29:46.483 --> 29:48.034
But you think it was the same man,

29:48.049 --> 29:51.865
this Mr. Kenworthy, who killed the woman
in pacific heights last night.

29:52.812 --> 29:54.793
But you haven't told the authorities.

29:55.577 --> 29:56.484
I will.

29:57.112 --> 29:58.405
I. I will.

29:58.835 --> 30:00.107
Soon as I'm sure.

30:02.169 --> 30:03.828
What?
Are those toys?

30:04.525 --> 30:07.605
Yeah, I've been seeing
a lot of children this week ever since.

30:07.620 --> 30:09.167
Ever since I went on television

30:09.431 --> 30:11.109
and said there is no Santa Claus.

30:13.250 --> 30:15.024
How are they doing, the kids?

30:15.101 --> 30:16.182
The kids are fine.

30:16.240 --> 30:18.304
Children are very resilient, Adrian.

30:19.474 --> 30:21.844
Although I might ask you to leave
by the side door today.

30:21.859 --> 30:22.877
I understand.

30:23.779 --> 30:25.766
They hate me. Everybody hates me.

30:27.827 --> 30:29.247
I thought I was alone before.

30:29.262 --> 30:30.664
I didn't know what alone meant.

30:30.704 --> 30:31.736
This is alone!

30:32.405 --> 30:33.407
Now I get it.

30:34.055 --> 30:35.212
Well, where's Natalie?

30:35.598 --> 30:38.297
She's at Randy Disher's christmas party
with everybody else.

30:38.355 --> 30:40.184
- You weren't invited?
- I was invited.

30:41.498 --> 30:43.466
I just...
don't want to see anyone.

30:45.753 --> 30:49.351
Adrian, I know how difficult this is
for you. I was worried about you even...

30:50.562 --> 30:54.417
Even before all this happened.
I know it's ten years since Trudy.

30:55.927 --> 30:56.930
Trudy.

30:57.362 --> 30:58.655
Trudy loved christmas.

30:59.238 --> 31:00.898
Yeah,
you mentioned that.

31:01.609 --> 31:02.851
Every christmas morning,

31:03.240 --> 31:04.607
she'd set the alarm.

31:06.347 --> 31:08.354
We'd go outside and watch the sun
come up.

31:10.233 --> 31:11.332
Trudy used to say...

31:12.795 --> 31:15.631
Christmas
made the whole world seem softer.

31:16.166 --> 31:17.201
Softer.

31:17.635 --> 31:18.639
I like that.

